The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mirzapur, Nov. 2 (PTI): A case of theft from an Indian Oil Corporation pipeline was reported today in Mirzapur.           
	The theft from the pipeline was detected after computer sensors of the IOC detected a major leakage between Allahabad and Mirzapur, superintendent of police Pretinder Singh said. He said the loss because of the theft could be in crores.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): The state pollution control has cracked down on water pollution near the Vaishnodevi shrine. It has sent notices to 42 hotels and restaurants near the temple for their failure to obtain licences from the board.                   
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): Two trekking agency owners were arrested on Saturday for allegedly sending trekkers to high altitudes in the Himalayas in Garhwal in spite of bad weather. Five porters died in September after getting caught in a blizzard, prompting the Uttarakhand government to order a probe.                   
	 Vadodara (PTI): A lioness and her three cubs were captured by forest officials on Sunday from a village in Gondal near Vadodara. The big cats had strayed from Sansagir sanctuary into the village seven days earlier and had killed five cows.                   
	 Kochi (PTI): A court in Kochi has granted conditional bail to a 23-year-old BTech student, arrested on the charge of sending an email to the President threatening the life of Congress president Sonia Gandhi. Arun Surya has been ordered to appear before the investigating officer once a week.                  
	 Lucknow: A group of monkeys forced a three-year-old boy to jump to his death from the third floor of his house in Lucknow on Saturday. The boys six-year-old sister, who too jumped after the children were attacked by the monkeys, was severely injured.                                                                                                                         
